course.subject: ECON
course.name: Industrial Organization and Regulations
course.description:
Industrial organization studies behavior of firms and industries, and their consequence in markets, mainly under imperfect competition. It also examines their implication for public policy including antitrust issues and industry
regulations. This course is graduate level introduction of theoretical foundation and empirical techniques in industrial organization.
course.prerequisites: ECON 5130 or ECON 5210
